title: Germany's Gotze ruled out of Euro qualifier against Georgia
text:
Germany's Gotze ruled out of Euro qualifier against Georgia Germany will be without Mario Gotze for Sunday's Euro 2016 qualifier against Georgia. 
Mario Gotze in action for Germany against the Republic of Ireland in Dublin on Thursday. Alexander Hassenstein / Bongarts/Getty Images Oct 9, 2015 at 11:52a ET 0Shares 
Germany will be without midfielder Mario Gotze for Sunday's Euro 2016 qualifier against Georgia. 
Gotze had to come off during the first half of Thursday's 1-0 loss to the Republic of Ireland in Dublin due to a groin problem. 
And Germany boss Joachim Low, quoted on www.dfb.de, said of the Bayern Munich man: "Mario Gotze will definitely not be playing on Sunday." 
No indication has been given at this stage of how bad the 23-year-old's injury might be. 
Meanwhile, Manchester United midfielder Bastian Schweinsteiger looks set to be unavailable as well for the weekend's Group D game in Leipzig. 
The 31-year-old sat out the Ireland match, reportedly because of a thigh injury, and Low added after the contest: "For Bastian Schweinsteiger we'll have to wait and see. The chances are slim though." 0
